00:31:22.060 --> 00:31:23.990
that we use for Gibbs free
energy are pressure and

00:31:23.990 --> 00:31:24.930
temperature.

00:31:24.930 --> 00:31:25.540
Right?

00:31:25.540 --> 00:31:28.000
So this is the variable that
goes with Gibbs free energy.

00:31:28.000 --> 00:31:31.902
So this means that they were
taking the derivatives of the

00:31:31.902 --> 00:31:34.280
Gibbs free energy with respect
to one of its variables is

00:31:34.280 --> 00:31:36.010
something that we should know.

00:31:36.010 --> 00:31:38.200
So we go back to writing what
the Gibbs free energy is.

00:31:38.200 --> 00:31:44.850
So dG is equal to
V dp minus S dT.

00:31:44.850 --> 00:31:46.670
Which is the fundamental
equation

00:31:46.670 --> 00:31:48.170
for Gibbs free energy.

00:31:48.170 --> 00:31:50.310
And this is the Gibbs free
energy per mole.

00:31:50.310 --> 00:31:53.730
That's just the chemical
potential.

00:31:53.730 --> 00:31:56.360
The same thing.

00:31:56.360 --> 00:31:58.950
And this is the derivative
with respect to pressure.

00:31:58.950 --> 00:32:01.380
And this is the derivative with
respect to temperature.

00:32:01.380 --> 00:32:05.890
So this thing here
is d mu / dp.

00:32:05.890 --> 00:32:08.250
At constant temperature.

00:32:08.250 --> 00:32:09.570
It's just the volume.

00:32:09.570 --> 00:32:12.300
So now we have this equation,
